  [1m[38;2;122;162;247m[details][0m[38;2;192;202;245m[48;2;26;27;38m                                                                                                             
  Codex review: keeping this open for maintainer follow-up; there is still a little grit to resolve.                    
                                                                                                                        
  Summary                                                                                                               
  Keep this open: current main still has a plausible Responses replay failure for custom openai-responses providers     
  because generic Responses payloads can be unstored while replaying server-owned reasoning item IDs. Direct OpenAI     
  routes have a newer store-aware wrapper, but the reported custom proxy route is not covered by that                   
  direct-OpenAI-only path.                                                                                              
                                                                                                                        
  Timeline by @osolmaz 2026-05-31T03:00:00Z                                                                             
  added label provider: openai-responses                                                                                
                                                                                                                        
  Comment by @tianxiaochannel-oss88 2026-05-31T04:10:00Z                                                                
  meta: association CONTRIBUTOR                                                                                         
  [1m[38;2;122;162;247m[details][0m[38;2;192;202;245m[48;2;26;27;38m                                                                                                             
  Adding a fresh macOS/Slack data point. I can reproduce this with a custom openai-responses provider when              
  previous_response_id is sent after an unstored first response. Removing the previous response reference makes the     
  next request succeed, which points at replay state rather than authentication or model availability.                  
                                                                                                                        
